menu "Luloc-ASTI: 2. Sensors - ADC Line Array"

    config LINE_SENSOR_CALIB_THRESHOLD
        int "Calibration Min-Max difference threshold"
        default 1500
        help
            The minimum difference between the maximum (white) and minimum (black) values
            read during calibration to consider a sensor successfully calibrated.
            For a 12-bit ADC (0-4095), 1500 is a safe threshold.

    config LINE_SENSOR_OVERSAMPLING
        int "ADC Oversampling count"
        default 16
        help
            Number of consecutive ADC reads to average for a single sensor measurement
            to increase precision and reduce noise. Higher values cost more CPU time.

    config LINE_SENSOR_DETECTION_THRESHOLD
        int "Digital Detection Threshold (%)"
        default 50
        help
            Percentage threshold (0-100) applied to the processed line signal.
            Values around 50 usually work best after a correct min-max calibration.

    config LINE_SENSOR_LINE_IS_DARK
        bool "Line color is dark (black)"
        default y
        help
            If enabled, the component inverts normalized reflectance so dark line
            produces high detection/weight. Disable only for white-line tracks
            on dark background.

endmenu
